# Contributing Guide

Thank you for your interest in contributing to this project!

## Getting Started

1. Fork the repository
2. Clone your fork
3. Create a feature branch

```bash
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
```

## Development Setup

```bash
# Install dependencies
cargo build

# Run tests
cargo test

# Run the formatter
cargo fmt

# Run the linter
cargo clippy
```

## Pull Request Checklist

Before submitting a PR, make sure you have:

- [x] Read this contributing guide
- [ ] Written tests for new functionality
- [ ] Run `cargo fmt` on all changed files
- [ ] Run `cargo clippy` with no warnings
- [ ] Updated documentation if needed
- [ ] Added a changelog entry

## Code Style

W> Do not use `unwrap()` in library code. Use proper error handling with `Result`.

T> Use `cargo clippy -- -W clippy::pedantic` for stricter linting.

## Commit Messages

Follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) format:

```
feat: add support for wiki embeds
fix: handle empty code blocks correctly
docs: update API reference
test: add fixtures for admonition parsing
```

## Issue Labels

| Label | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `bug` | Something is not working |
| `feature` | New feature request |
| `docs` | Documentation improvement |
| `good first issue` | Suitable for newcomers |

## Questions?

Open a [Discussion](https://github.com/example/markright/discussions) or reach out on [Discord](https://discord.gg/markright).
